member.summary:
Creates a  instance as its bit representation via the specified  instance;
with overflow checking - throws  if the argument uses exceeded bits
whose position is greater than 81.

member.remarks:
Two  values can be compared with each other. If one of those two is an elimination
(i.e. holds the value  as the type), the instance will be greater;
if those two hold same conclusion type, but one of those two holds the global index of the candidate position is greater, it is greater.

Two  values can be compared with each other. If one of those two is an elimination
(i.e. holds the value  as the type), the instance will be greater;
if those two hold same conclusion type, but one of those two holds the global index of the candidate position is greater, it is greater.

member.summary:
Indicates the conclusion type of the current instance.
If the type is , this conclusion will be set value (Set a digit into a cell);
otherwise, a candidate will be removed.

param.para:
This value can contain 1 or 81 elements.
If the array contain 1 element, all elements in the target sudoku grid will be initialized by it, the uniform value;
if the array contain 81 elements, elements will be initialized by the array one by one using the array elements respectively.

member.remarks:
The type of the current collection supports using -like expression to determine whether the collection is not empty,
for example:

if (collection)
    // ...

The statement collection will be expanded to collection.Count != 0. Therefore, the negation operator !
will invert the result of above expression. This is why I use  ! to determine on this.
